            Well there isn&#39;t any goal actually. Coming to the red dot simply 

triggers &quot;You found the solution!&quot; thing, nothing more. It is 

interesting that, when I remove random walls from the maze during the 

never-ending loop of displaying the solution, although it doesn&#39;t 

reach the goal every time, it still avoids the walls, it almost never 

crashes (colliding with a wall means death in this version). So NEAT 

based Novelty Search actually finds a policy of behavior that leads 

the individual to the goal as a consequence of it, i.e. it doesn&#39;t 

learn every piece of the maze. But sometimes individuals do get 

confused when some walls are gone, which implies that it is the 

particular genotype that is important. Many can navigate that maze, 

even without hidden nodes. Some of them are general solutions capable 

of navigating any kind of maze, but others are dependant on the 

configuration of this particular maze. 



Peter C



